        <section id="what-is-hyper">
            <h5>What is hyper</h5>
            <p>Hyper is a lite <a class="theme-link scrollto" href="#mvc">mvc</a>-based php framework with many other
                capabilities that will enable you, the developer
                to develop websites and web-apps with much dynamism and speed as possible. The idea was inspired by
                the need for a structured code in php and not using some huge frameworks even for a small thing.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="mvc">
            <h5>Model-View-Controller(MVC)</h5>
            <p>The View acts as GUI, Model Acts as Back End and Control acts as an adapter. Here three parts are
                interconnected with each other. It will pass the data and access the data between each other.</p>
            <p>MVC is a concept of creating pages that are driven by a given model with the the controller doing all the
                heavy work. The main reason for this kind of approach is separation of concerns.</p>
            <p>So then to simplify stuff we will give you the task to create models and from these models we create your
                database tables then render your pages using <a class="theme-link scrollto" href="#twig">Twig templating
                    engine</a>. Your controllers control what to
                visit or what to show when what link is visited</p>
        </section>

        <section id="twig">
            <h5>Twig Templating Engine</h5>
            <p>Twig is a template language for PHP, released under the new BSD license (code
                and documentation). Twig uses a syntax similar to the Django and Jinja template languages which
                inspired the Twig runtime environment.</p>
            <p>Visit the <a class="theme-link" href="https://twig.symphony.com">official site</a> for more and <a
                        class="theme-link" href="https://twig.symfony.com/documentation">documentation</a></p>
        </section>

