    <section class="docs-section" id="why-hyper">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Why hyper?</h2>
        <p>One might be tempted to ask "Why should i use this hyper thingy?",</p>
        <p>Well there is probably a countless number
            of <code>php mvc</code> frameworks out there which offer even better stuff, but fortunately enough you're
            here so let me give you reasons to stay:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Have you ever just gotten irritated by the urls that always ended up saying something something .php or
                .html, if yes then you've come to the right place.
            </li>
            <li>Or are you tired of defining routes that should hide your app file structure? Hyper does that for you,
                no more to defining an endless array of routes
                <p>Just say: {{ highlight("new \Hyper\Application\HyperApp('SuperCoolAppName')")|raw }} and watch the
                    magic happen.</p>
            </li>
            <li>Do you get bored of writing all long "quoted SQL" when you just want to add a simple object to your
                database ?
                <p>How does this look?</p>
                <code class="d-block docs-code-block">
                    {{ highlight("
                        $db = new DatabaseContext('singular::of::table');

                        //INSERT INTO [plural::of::table](...) VALUES(...)
                        $db->add($myObject);

                        //SELECT * FROM [plural::of::table]
                        $db->all(/* optional [columns]*/);

                        //UPDATE [plural::of::table] SET ...
                        $db->update($updatedObject);

                        //DELETE WHERE ...<br>
                        $db->delete($entity, /* [bool $softDelete, bool $deleteAll] */);

                        # search, pagination, where...and many more
                    ")|raw }}
                </code>
            </li>
            <li>You tired of writing structureless code? Come lets do it with <a class="scrollto theme-link"
                                                                                 href="#mvc">Model-View-Controller</a>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>Now that, that's out of our way lets go to the <a class="scrollto theme-link" href="#getting-started">good
                stuff</a></p>
